GASTROENTERITIS - NORWAY (03): (BUSKERUD) ENTEROTOXIGENIC E. COLI
*****************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 21 Dec 2012
From: Joanne Michelle Ocampo <jfo36@georgetown.edu>


On Fri 21 Dec 2012 the Norwegian Institute of Public Health released new information about the gastroenteritis outbreak in Buskerud, Norway. New cases of illness have not been reported since Sun 9 Dec 2012. The Institute therefore declared that the outbreak is over.

[Enterotoxigenic] _Escherichia coli_ (ETEC) has been isolated from patients, but not from food products or water sources. Surveys, however, indicate that contaminated food products may have been the vehicle of transmission.

Both travel and non-travel associated ETEC outbreaks are uncommon in Scandinavian countries. Until recently, outbreaks caused by ETEC have not been reported in Norway.

For the original article (in Norwegian), please see http://www.fhi.no/eway/default.aspx?pid=233&trg=Area_5774&MainArea_5661=5588:0:15,1787:1:0:0:::0:0&MainLeft_5588=5774:0:15,1787:1:0:0:::0:0&Area_5774=5544:100555::1:5776:1:::0:0.

