[ProMED-mail thanks Joanne Ocampo for providing additional information about this large outbreak of gastroenteritis at a Norwegian hotel.

The outbreak affected 319 people attending a Christmas Party, but no further cases have been detected since 9 Dec 2012. Enterotoxigenic _Escherichia coli (ETEC) has been isolated from patients who attended the Christmas Party at the hotel, and norovirus is no longer considered to be the culprit. The source of the outbreak remains uncertain, however, as the agent has not been isolated from food or water sources at the hotel. It is presumed, however, that a contaminated food product may have been the culprit since non-travel associated ETEC outbreaks have been uncommon in Scandinavian countries.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/4uHH. - Mod.CP]
